        ... initialization of more registers ...
    }

The implementation in `...__1__Slow.cpp` looks very suspicuous to me since this is an unguarded recursive call to the function.
I tried to look at the verilator source code to understand how it generates the name of the `eval_initial` functions but do not know, where the final index comes from.

Unfortunately, the project that I'm using verilator on is quite convoluted so I have not been able to extract a reproducer. I would need some hints to know where to actually look for the problem.


